data.description:
Impeccably maintained 2 bedroom 2 bathroom condominium at the L Haus is offered for sale.
From the moment you enter this gorgeous home, you're struck by the soaring ceilings, flawless design and artistic touches that grace this owner occupied home.  Some of the unique qualities to the home are the 11' 8" ceilings that are available only on the 6th floor, the impeccable condition of the unit including  all surfaces, hardwood floors, hardware & cabinets, rare and fantastic Manhattan views to the west for everyday enjoyment and special viewing opportunities of the NYC Marathon & Macy's 4th of July Fireworks, and the open modern chef's kitchen with island.
The open kitchen is the centerpiece of the home with plentiful cabinet storage and counter space. To the left is the second bathroom and utility closet with stacked Washer Dryer units and storage. The second bedroom is currently outfitted as a library /reading room with a pull-out Murphy's bed and expansive closet and wall space thanks to the soaring ceilings. 
The master lies to the right of the living room and easily accommodates a king size bed and dresser.  There are 2 rows of built out closets and an ensuite primary bath with shower, tub and double vanities.
This meticulously maintained home is offered for resale for the first time. The L Haus is a full service luxury condominium in the heart of Long Island city, and rests just 2 blocks from the #7 train which is one stop away from Grand Central and all other connecting trains. The building's amenities include a fitness center, 24 hour doorman, children's playroom, resident lounge, outdoor garden, roofdeck with 360 degree views of NYC and an on site parking garage where spaces can be rented or purchased.
